FAQs
What are the benefits of studying medicine in Malaysia?
Malaysia offers high-quality education, affordable tuition fees, English-taught programs, excellent clinical training, and a diverse, multicultural environment.

How can Qadri-International help me study medicine in Malaysia?
Qadri-International provides comprehensive guidance, application assistance, visa support, financial planning, and pre-departure and post-arrival support to ensure a smooth study abroad experience.

Are there English-taught medical programs in Malaysia?
Yes, many medical programs in Malaysia are taught in English, making them accessible to international students.

What are the costs associated with studying medicine in Malaysia?
Tuition fees range from $10,000 to $25,000 per year, and living expenses average between $3,000 and $6,000 per year. Scholarships and financial aid are available to help reduce these costs.

How do I apply to Malaysian medical schools?
The application process involves submitting an online application form, academic transcripts, a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and proof of language proficiency. Qadri-International can assist with each step of the application process.
